Have you got a sex or relationship question but don’t know who to ask? Or maybe a dating dilemma that needs some expert advice? Whatever your concern, whether it’s a first date, an awkward sex question or a long-term relationship issue, and wherever you are on the relationship spectrum, our new agony aunt, the brilliant Laura Collins, wants to hear from you. Each week, our experts advise daters on all sorts of sex, love, and romance struggles as part of The Sex Column. Previous dilemmas tackled by The Sex Column include a reader stuck in a sexless relationship with a cheating girlfriend, a woman struggling with her husband’s bipolar disorder and a case of serial ghosting. That means we’ve really seen it all – so you won’t face any judgment here, just excellent advice from experts who know their stuff. Want to get involved and get your problem sorted? Just send your issue to Laura.Collins@metro.co.uk. For more sex and relationships content join Jackie Adedeji and Miranda Kane for our weekly sex positive podcast: Smut Drop. It’s a whole new world of sexpertise where no topic is off limits. MORE : ‘I’ve been dumped twice – am I driving partners away?’ MORE : ‘My partner never says sorry – what do I do?’